definition.value: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any steroidal carboxylic acid.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (2S)-gluphosinate (better known as gluphosinate-P) and (2R)-gluphosinate.
A nanotube primarily composed of H2Ti3O7 where the H atoms can be substituted by metal atoms.
The R enantiomer of nomifensine.
muco-Quinic acid in which the hydroxy functions at C-3 and C-5 have been esterified with trans-caffeic acid.
A member of the class of  benzimidazoles that is 1H-benzimidazole substituted by a pyrrolidin-1-ylmethyl and a 4-chlorobenzyl groups at positions 2 and 1 respectively.
A carbon oxoacid that consists of 1,2-diketocyclobut-3-ene bearing two enolic hydroxy substituents at positions 3 and 4.
Any glycosyloxyflavone that consists of a flavonol attached to a beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.
Any glycosyloxyflavone that consists of a flavonol attached to a beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.
Any glycosyloxyflavone that consists of a flavonol attached to a beta-D-glucosyl residue at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.
The ion formed by protonating nitrogen in pyrrolidine.
An aromatic amine that is 2-phenylethanamine in which one of the hydrogens attached to the amino group is substituted by a benzyl group.
A member of the class of ethanolamines that is aminoethanol in which the hydrogens of the amino group are replaced by ethyl groups.
An organic cation that is the monoprotonated form of procaine.
A benzoxadiazole that is 2,1,3-benzoxadiazole  which is substituted at positions 4 and 7 by (5-carboxypentyl)amino and nitro groups, respectively.
An organic chloride salt having 5-amino-9-(diethylamino)benzo[a]phenoxazin-7-ium as the couterion. fluorescent dye which is also a potent photosensitiser for photodynamic therapy.

An organic cation that is 6a,12a-dihydrobenzo[a]phenoxazin-7-ium substituted by amino and dimethylamino groups at positions 5 and 9 respectively. The chloride salt is the histological dye 'nile blue A'
An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 5H-benzo[a]phenoxazin-5-one substituted at position 9 by a diethylamino group.
A substituted porphyrin compound containing one or more halogen atoms.
A substituted porphyrin compound containing one or more bromine atoms.
A porphyrin compound substituted with one or more bromine atoms bonded to a pyrrole group of the porphyrin ring.
